            <para>Since the ESC has electronically programmable inputs and outputs, ESC configuration will vary from
                vehicle to vehicle.
            </para>
            <para>The ESC is mounted in the dash panel between the cab and the engine compartment. It has a power
                connector, from switched ignition, inside the cab and a power connector, from the batteries, in the
                engine compartment.
            </para>
            <para>Power for components controlled by switches and the switch packs is supplied from the ESC.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The ESC is not a repairable module. Once it has been determined that the ESC has an internal
                        malfunction, it must be replaced and the replacement must be programmed. There is a chance that
                        reloading the programming might repair some problems.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
